#: ../../config/options_player.rst:4
msgid ""
":index:`Audio Player Options <pair: configuration; audio player; "
"listenbrainz>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:19
msgid "**Enable audio player \"now playing\" notifications**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:21
msgid ""
"When enabled, Picard will send \"now playing\" notifications from the "
"internal audio player. The availability of this option depends on the "
"operating system. Currently this is available for macOS and on Linux."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:23
msgid "**Submit listens to ListenBrainz**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:25
msgid ""
"When enabled, Picard will submit listened tracks to your `ListenBrainz "
"<https://listenbrainz.org>`_ profile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:27
msgid "**Submit only tagged files**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:29
msgid ""
"When enabled, Picard will only submit tracks that have been tagged with "
"MusicBrainz metadata. This option is enabled by default, as untagged files "
"often have missing or incorrect metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:31
msgid "**ListenBrainz user token**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:33
msgid ""
"Enter your ListenBrainz user token here to enable listen submission to your "
"profile. You can find your token on your `ListenBrainz settings page "
"<https://listenbrainz.org/settings/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:38
msgid ""
"The Audio Player options are only available if the built-in audio player is "
"available. The player can be unavailable if the system is missing the "
"required Qt Multimedia libraries. It can also be disabled with the ``--no-"
"player`` command line option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_player.rst:42
msgid ":doc:`../appendices/command_line`"
msgstr ""
